gomodel:SYNGO_3802  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig. 1. NPY inhibits 4AP- and KCl-evoked glutamate release from rat cerebrocortical synaptosomes\nFig. 2. NPY-mediated inhibition of 4AP-evoked glutamate release is mimicked by the selective NPY Y1 receptor agonist and is blocked by the selective NPY Y1 receptor antagonist.\nFig. 4. Release inhibition by NPY is due to a reduction in the depolarization-evoked rise in [Ca2+]C.\nFig. 5. NPY does not alter the synaptosomal membrane potential.. Experimental description: - \"Synaptosomes were purified as described previously (Sihra, 1997). Briefly, the cerebral cortex from 2-month-old male Sprague-Dawley rats\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2018-06-28" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_3802" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

